author: @sbern42
text: So, in bash: "find repos -type f ! -name '*.py' -exec rm {} \;"  i.e. in "repos"  - recursively list all files (-type f)  - that do not end with ".py" ( ! -name '*.py' )   - and delete them (-exec rm {} \;)

author: @RecursiveTriforce
text: tqdm didn't have a progress bar because os.walk is an iterator.   It doesn't have a length.  You could have called it as: tqdm(os.walk(...), total=1000000)  Then it assumes that there are a million iterations in total.
